snippet.textDisplay: As a Bengali with roots in Bangladesh living in India, this song affects me in the same way as it would affect any displaced human. The language doesn't matter, Maan saab's voice matters and as Raavi asks Chenab how is Satluj doing, so does the Hooghly asks Padma how is Meghna doing. Makes me keep coming back for that one line "Raavi ton chenab puchda ki haal hai satluj da"
snippet.textOriginal: As a Bengali with roots in Bangladesh living in India, this song affects me in the same way as it would affect any displaced human. The language doesn't matter, Maan saab's voice matters and as Raavi asks Chenab how is Satluj doing, so does the Hooghly asks Padma how is Meghna doing. Makes me keep coming back for that one line "Raavi ton chenab puchda ki haal hai satluj da"
